=> RAG Pipeline Documentation

1. Definition

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) combines:
i) Vector retrieval
ii) Contextual reasoning
iii) Optimized output generation


2. Pipeline Steps

Step 1: Query Creation
User requests:
"Schedule 30 minute meeting"
Converted to:
"User scheduling preferences for 30 minute meeting"

Step 2: Embedding Generation
Query â†’ 384 dimensional embedding vector

Step 3: Vector Search
FAISS retrieves top-k similar memory items.
These may include:
i) User preferences
ii) Past scheduling behavior
iii) Calendar summaries

Step 4: Context Assembly
Retrieved metadata compiled into context block.

Step 5: Slot Generation
Scheduler computes:
i) Free intervals
ii) Valid duration slots

Step 6: Optimization
Slots ranked using:
Score = PreferenceWeight - ConflictPenalty


3. Latency Optimization

i) In-memory vector search
ii)  Pre-compressed calendar data
iii) No external API calls
iv) Minimal context size
